race.description: Robert Biffin Ttc Hall Of Fame Inductee Handicap (C2)
race.comment: LADY GALADRIEL (3) raced close to the pace and battled on well to finish third as a short-priced favourite when resuming from a spell over 1200m here 23 days ago. She has won both of her tune-up trials before that and will be spot-on with her fitness now. She drops 3.5kg and can take this out. Follow your money. FLUFFY'S GIRL (8) returns from a six-month spell and has her first start for the Christie Burt stable. Her form on the mainland was good, and a recent trial win will ensure that she is ready to rumble fresh up. BLAMEITONTHEBOOGIE  (1) was runner-up over 1000m at Hobart last time out. He was unbeaten in starts before that, and will be hard to hold out again, especially with the aid of the pole position. HARTMAN (4) is an ex-Queensland gelding who was put aside after winning his first local start on the Devonport poly track. Watch closely, fresh up. LAST TREMBLE (9) hasn't been seen since finishing fifth over 1400m at Hobart seven months ago, but she is worth keeping safe.
